KwaZulu-Natal police have announced that yet another suspect has been arrested for a shooting at the notoriously dangerous Glebelands Hostel. Police said a 38-year-old suspect was arrested for attempted murder at Bayhead. It is alleged that on 31 August 2017 at 20:45, a 45-year-old man was at Block P in the Glebelands Hostel when he was allegedly shot by a known suspect,” the statement said. “He sustained gunshots wounds to the head, shoulder and abdomen. The victim managed to seek assistance after the shooting and police officers that were in the vicinity responded to the incident. The victim was taken to hospital for medical attention. “The suspect fled the scene and has been on the run since then.” Police said the suspect was arrested while at work in Bayhead. He will appear in the Umlazi Magistrate’s Court on Thursday on a charge of attempted murder. eNCA